      • searchForDetailedPictures

        public java.util.List<DetailedPictureModel> searchForDetailedPictures​(DetailedPictureModel model)
        This Method accepts the "DetailedPictureModel" model. The model is a composition of three sub-models, namely: PictureModel, IPTCModel, EXIFModel, PhotographerModel This given model is passed to the DAL layer where the contents of the model are expected to be used as search parameters. (query building...)
        Parameters:
        model - The model containing the parameters used to perform the search operation!
        Returns:
        A list of found "DetailedPictureModel" instances. (:= rows of the sql query)

      • saveDetailedPicture

        public void saveDetailedPicture​(DetailedPictureModel model)
        This method simply hands the given model to the underlying DAL layer to perform a generic "save" procedure. If the model id is set then the model with this id will simply be overwritten... If however the getId method of the given model returns null, then the DAL is expected to store the model as a new entry. (It is also expected to set the id of the given model)
        Parameters:
        model - The model which ought to be saved.
